y, a children's story,2500:00:15,640 --> 00:00:18,760And the next day, when we were looking back at the news2600:00:18,760 --> 00:00:21,600And he asked me again what I did was tell him a story.2700:00:21,600 --> 00:00:24,280I want to share it with you.2800:00:24,280 --> 00:00:29,560I tell you, I told Nina that day that there was once a very quiet town2900:00:03,240 --> 00:00:06,280And there was a boy named Pepe, the protagonist, who lived in the house farthest from the village.3000:00:06,280 --> 00:00:10,040One afternoon, Pepe went for a walk and got thirsty.3100:00:10,040 --> 00:00:12,680When he came home, he opened a bottle of wine,3200:00:12,680 --> 00:00:15,800And while he was drinking the wine he discovered something3300:00:15,800 --> 00:00:18,400that no one had ever discovered.3400:00:18,400 --> 00:00:22,120There were no bars in the village, there was not even a bar.3500:00:22,120 --> 00:00:24,480Pepe thought if he opened a bar,3600:00:24,480 --> 00:00:27,800I could make others happy by giving them to drink,3700:00:03,440 --> 00:00:07,120And besides, he also thought he could make some money, and he was happy with the idea of opening a bar.3800:00:07,120 --> 00:00:10,140That afternoon his friend Moncho passed by Pepe's house.3900:00:10,140 --> 00:00:13,340And gave it a good name for the bar.4000:00:13,340 --> 00:00:16,620And you know that when a nightmare idea has a name,4100:00:16,620 --> 00:00:19,960That idea is starting to roll.4200:00:19,960 --> 00:00:22,260So Pepe made a list of needs.4300:00:22,260 --> 00:00:24,260To open the first bar in town.4400:00:24,260 --> 00:00:26,320Nina was looking at me with her eyes open.4500:00:26,320 --> 00:00:28,760The story was good so far.4600:00:03,440 --> 00:00:07,960Pepe realized that since he bought tables, chairs, cups, paint, a bar stool for bar customers to put their horses4700:00:07,960 --> 00:00:09,640And they could enter and drink,4800:00:09,640 --> 00:00:13,920And he took out the bills and all that was going to cost him about 10,000 coins.4900:00:13,920 --> 00:00:17,280Of course, Pepe didn't have 10,000 coins because he was poor,5000:00:17,280 --> 00:00:21,880But overnight, he figured out a way to get those 10,000 coins.5100:00:21,880 --> 00:00:24,720Pepe cut a thousand paperbacks5200:00:02,880 --> 00:00:05,380And he wrote on each piece of paper the phrase, soon Bar de Pepe.5300:00:05,380 --> 00:00:07,480He wrote that a thousand times.5400:00:07,480 --> 00:00:11,000And on Sunday after Mass he went to the People's Square,5500:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,800Dressed in her best suit,5600:00:12,800 --> 00:00:16,380And he said to all the neighbors in the square,5700:00:16,380 --> 00:00:20,140Dear neighbors, I'm opening a bar outside the village.5800:00:20,140 --> 00:00:21,580Everybody looked at him.5900:00:21,580 --> 00:00:23,480What a good idea! Some said.6000:00:23,480 --> 00:00:25,980Pepe felt great with everyone's attention.6100:00:25,980 --> 00:00:28,000And then he showed in a fan.6200:00:03,400 --> 00:00:06,840The thousand paper clips and she said, this is important, Nina told her I said, Pepe said,6300:00:06,840 --> 00:00:10,600Each of these 1,000 pieces of paper costs 10 coins,6400:00:10,600 --> 00:00:12,800The neighbors were looking at him.6500:00:12,800 --> 00:00:16,040Whoever buys me a little piece of paper is gonna have to keep it.6600:00:16,040 --> 00:00:19,080Because in a month, when I open my bar,6700:00:19,080 --> 00:00:22,720I'm gonna pay 12 coins for each piece of paper.6800:00:22,720 --> 00:00:25,120I want you to give me back.6900:00:25,120 --> 00:00:27,480Then there was whispering all over the square7000:00:03,760 --> 00:00:06,440And Moncho, who was the fool of the town, asked, for Pepe, but it doesn't cost 10 coins each piece of paper,7100:00:06,440 --> 00:00:09,280Why are you gonna give away two more coins afterwards?7200:00:09,280 --> 00:00:12,560And Pepe said, it's not giving, Moncho, it's compensating.7300:00:12,560 --> 00:00:15,360I'll make up for it with two more coins.7400:00:15,360 --> 00:00:19,120To help me fulfill my dream, which is to open a bar.7500:00:19,120 --> 00:00:22,560Then the mayor who was out there came up and said,7600:00:22,560 --> 00:00:26,280It makes sense, it makes a lot of sense, all right, Pepe.7700:00:04,260 --> 00:00:06,720And Ernesto, who was rich and knew business, said, "I think the idea is very good.7800:00:06,720 --> 00:00:10,640And the priest Richard, taking some coins from under his cellar,7900:00:10,640 --> 00:00:13,940He said, "It's a very Christian idea.8000:00:13,940 --> 00:00:16,820I want some of your paperwork,8100:00:16,820 --> 00:00:20,820And everybody started buying Pepe's paper.8200:00:20,820 --> 00:00:24,480In such a simple way and in one morning,8300:00:24,480 --> 00:00:26,660Pepe got the money to open his bar.8400:00:26,660 --> 00:00:29,640Among all the neighbors, they bought him the thousand papers.8500:00:03,360 --> 00:00:08,560I bought him two, Sabino said, he was poor but optimistic, I bought him 36, he was screaming here, he was greedy and arrogant.8600:00:08,560 --> 00:00:11,640Pepe went home with 10,000 coins in his backpack.8700:00:11,640 --> 00:00:15,080And he fell asleep thinking about his dream of opening a bar.8800:00:15,080 --> 00:00:18,640The next day was Monday and Pepe traveled to town.8900:00:18,640 --> 00:00:22,720And he bought wood to build a counter and he bought paint.9000:00:22,720 --> 00:00:25,240He went home and got to work.9100:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,240He didn't go through town square for the next four weeks.9200:00:07,240 --> 00:00:13,360Pepe didn't know about the disaster that was gonna happen because of his paperwork.9300:00:13,360 --> 00:00:15,880At that moment in the story I brake9400:00:15,880 --> 00:00:19,320And I just sat there and looked at my daughter to see if she was understanding the story.9500:00:19,320 --> 00:00:22,800You always have to test the metaphors with the kids,9600:00:22,800 --> 00:00:25,040Especially when they're complex ideas.9700:00:25,040 --> 00:00:26,560And she said to me, Dad,9800:00:26,560 --> 00:00:29,520This has nothing to do with what the hairy man on the TV said,9900:00:02,000 --> 00:00:08,000So I told him what happened in the village during the first week.10000:00:09,000 --> 00:00:14,000That Monday, the square was crowded, far more than a normal Monday.10100:00:14,000 --> 00:00:20,000Many neighbors had spent the night cutting their own paperwork10200:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,000Because they also discovered they had projects.10300:00:23,000 --> 00:00:26,000which they could not meet due to lack of money.10400:00:05,600 --> 00:00:09,700Some papillots said, briefly, Horace's hairdresser.10500:00:09,700 --> 00:00:13,320And there were even some papers written by Moncho,10600:00:13,320 --> 00:00:15,680with misspellings, saying,10700:00:15,680 --> 00:00:17,980I'm going to the moon at the end of the month.10800:00:17,980 --> 00:00:22,680Suddenly the neighbors went up to the streetlights,10900:00:22,680 --> 00:00:26,100So the other neighbors could buy those little papers,11000:00:26,100 --> 00:00:29,980They went up to the fountain, to exchange paper for coins,11100:00:05,660 --> 00:00:06,660Tuesday was even worse and on Wednesday you couldn't walk through the quilombo square.11200:00:11,560 --> 00:00:16,300The mayor had to put order and enabled a closed place in the municipality so that the neighbors could gather to exchange papers without destroying the square.11300:00:16,300 --> 00:00:21,800This small venue opened on Thursday and was named the Hall of the Papelites.11400:00:22,320 --> 00:00:25,300And so it was that on Friday, everyone who had a project11500:00:25,300 --> 00:00:28,960They had already gotten the coins they needed to carry it out.11600:00:01,400 --> 00:00:05,200Horace was already looking for milk, cream, ice for his ice cream shop,11700:00:05,200 --> 00:00:08,500Pepe was already scraping wood for the bar counter,11800:00:08,500 --> 00:00:11,600Carmen sharpened the scissors for her flamboyant hairdresser11900:00:11,600 --> 00:00:16,200And Moncho had bought two thin horses to go to the moon.12000:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,200Only a group of neighbors stayed in the paperwork room.12100:00:22,200 --> 00:00:27,200who had never in their lives thought of any interesting project.12200:00:05,500 --> 00:00:09,380All these neighbors had were other people's paperwork.12300:00:09,380 --> 00:00:11,080Oh, my God, he said.12400:00:11,080 --> 00:00:14,040Now I need money to buy cigarettes and I don't have it.12500:00:14,040 --> 00:00:19,740A few days ago, I traded my last 10 coins for a little Pepe paper and now I need to smoke.12600:00:19,740 --> 00:00:23,840I want to go to the movies, I don't have a dime.12700:00:23,840 --> 00:00:25,940The complaints grew.12800:00:04,800 --> 00:00:09,520Until Sabino, who was clever, raised his little piece of paper and said, "Look, guys, in three weeks Pepe will pay you twelve coins.12900:00:09,520 --> 00:00:12,620Who gives back this little piece of paper I bought for ten.13000:00:12,620 --> 00:00:16,680I'm selling my little paper right now for eight coins.13100:00:16,680 --> 00:00:19,560And the others looked at him and said, "Ah!13200:00:19,560 --> 00:00:23,240Deal made Ernesto said, he was rich but wanted to make even richer13300:00:23,240 --> 00:00:27,680And he took the little piece of paper out of his hands for eight pieces of silver.13400:00:03,480 --> 00:00:07,120Ramon and Luis also sold their paperwork for less than 10 coins and while one was running to buy cigarettes and the other was going to the movies,13500:00:07,120 --> 00:00:11,040The other neighbors saw that this was a new way of doing business,13600:00:11,040 --> 00:00:15,360Even if they never had a real idea in their life.13700:00:15,360 --> 00:00:19,520Some went up to chairs, others to tables, and they began to offer what they had,13800:00:19,520 --> 00:00:24,440Even the priest Richard came from the church sad and said,13900:00:03,040 --> 00:00:07,