 in the construction of his bar,18200:00:19,560 --> 00:00:23,480But other papers were not wanted by anyone, for example those of Moncho,18300:00:23,480 --> 00:00:26,760Because their artifact for making trips to the moon for the time being18400:00:26,760 --> 00:00:29,440It consisted of only two horses and a chariot.18500:00:03,960 --> 00:00:07,120No one thought that would start flying.18600:00:07,120 --> 00:00:08,680During the first week,18700:00:08,680 --> 00:00:12,640Now he wanted to get rid of Moncho's papers.18800:00:12,640 --> 00:00:15,280And since he also had Pepe's papers,18900:00:15,280 --> 00:00:20,640He invented something very good, which he named the beads of Ernesto.19000:00:20,640 --> 00:00:23,560They were sealed packages with 100 papers of all colors.19100:00:23,560 --> 00:00:26,960For example, there were 10 papers from Pepe's bar upstairs,19200:00:03,120 --> 00:00:08,36020 papers from the estate of Horace to the Middle and 70 papers from the Moncho Lunar project below,19300:00:08,360 --> 00:00:10,560without anyone seeing.19400:00:10,560 --> 00:00:12,160Thursday of the second week,19500:00:12,160 --> 00:00:14,640Ernesto's bands were very successful.19600:00:14,640 --> 00:00:16,560Among the neighbors who were looking like crazy19700:00:16,560 --> 00:00:18,800Pepe or the mayor's paperwork,19800:00:18,800 --> 00:00:22,480But on Friday Quique discovered the trick and said,19900:00:22,480 --> 00:00:24,560Watch out neighbors, watch out.20000:00:24,560 --> 00:00:26,360Ernesto's beads sometimes come20100:00:26,360 --> 00:00:29,160With Pepe or Mayor's papers on the top.20200:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,200And that's okay, but the bottom of the package and a bunch of monk papers that never in a fucking life is gonna be any trip to the moon.20300:00:07,200 --> 00:00:10,620So before you buy Ernesto's beads, you should ask my advice.20400:00:10,620 --> 00:00:14,760My fee for each council is two coins.20500:00:14,760 --> 00:00:19,820Since then, paper buyers have always consulted Kike before buying.20600:00:19,820 --> 00:00:21,800I'm not sure what I'm talking about.20700:00:21,800 --> 00:00:27,600Ernesto and Kike, who had been friends for many years, stopped talking forever.20800:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,960And so it was the second week.20900:00:04,600 --> 00:00:08,160I explained to her that in the real world, the official papers of the21000:00:08,160 --> 00:00:11,360Mayor is called public debt securities,21100:00:11,360 --> 00:00:14,400I explained to him that Ernesto's knives are named after21200:00:14,400 --> 00:00:18,360Debt obligations, while Kike's house,21300:00:18,360 --> 00:00:21,120The place where neighbors go to know if they trust or not21400:00:21,120 --> 00:00:25,240Ernesto's knives, they're called investment banking.21500:00:25,240 --> 00:00:29,080So I told Nina that when the third week started in21600:00:05,400 --> 00:00:10,720Pepe had only to nail the plow so that the neighbours' horses would graze21700:00:10,720 --> 00:00:15,800Horace had managed to beat milk and fruit for his ice cream shop and nothing else.21800:00:15,800 --> 00:00:20,720She had to bring ice bars from the city.21900:00:20,720 --> 00:00:24,960He found a good place to set up his hairdresser, even though he already had dozens of scissors.22000:00:06,040 --> 00:00:11,800And what can I say about Moncho, poor Moncho, his horses were getting weaker and weaker, even though he brushed him day and night and it didn't seem like his artifact could fly.22100:00:11,800 --> 00:00:17,920Neighbors who had Moncho or Carmen's papers were restless.22200:00:17,920 --> 00:00:24,000And they couldn't sell themselves to anyone anymore until Kike came up with a great idea.22300:00:05,680 --> 00:00:11,960Whoever still has Moncho's papers don't worry, I can sell you Quique's tranquility for those papers.22400:00:11,960 --> 00:00:16,720He had a lot of Moncho papers.22500:00:16,720 --> 00:00:21,700He pays me two coins every night from here at the end of the month.22600:00:21,700 -