 secretary puts a note on each project,24800:00:09,360 --> 00:00:13,240In the real world, they're called rating agencies.24900:00:13,240 --> 00:00:17,960Sometimes they're wrong unintentionally and sometimes they're wrongly.25000:00:17,960 --> 00:00:22,080Then Nina asked me if Pepe had finally managed to open his bar,25100:00:22,080 --> 00:00:24,320Because we were already in the fourth week,25200:00:24,320 --> 00:00:26,800And I told him the end of the story.25300:00:26,800 --> 00:00:28,720The end of the story says so.25400:00:03,060 --> 00:00:06,960When the fourth week came and the month was complete, Pepe got up very early and walked quietly to the village.25500:00:06,960 --> 00:00:12,340From a distance, you could see the facade of his bar with the bright sign all clothed.25600:00:12,340 --> 00:00:16,900The bar was called La Luna, as Moncho had named it the first day.25700:00:16,900 --> 00:00:20,240Now all that was left was for the neighbors to come on horseback.25800:00:20,240 --> 00:00:22,560with their throats dead of thirst.25900:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,400Pepe went all the way to the village,26000:00:25,400 --> 00:00:28,400Putting signs on every tree on the road.26100:00:02,800 --> 00:00:08,000Barla Luna, open every night, every sign he put on, he went far and he was proud looking at the sign.26200:00:09,400 --> 00:00:15,800However, when he arrived at the People's Square, he did not understand anything about what was happening.26300:00:16,300 --> 00:00:19,600He even thought he'd gone wrong and that he was in a different town.26400:00:19,600 --> 00:00:23,100It seemed that the war had passed through that town.26500:00:23,400 --> 00:00:26,300The lanterns and fountains of the Square were all destroyed.26600:00:05,540 --> 00:00:09,300There was not a single horse in the streets and the neighbors walked round, talking alone. What happened here? asked Pepe Horacio when he saw him.26700:00:09,300 --> 00:00:11,620"Oh, Pepe!" said Horace, crying.26800:00:11,620 --> 00:00:18,000Everyone went crazy with the papers with mine, with Carmen's, with yours.26900:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,000With everyone, all of a sudden, he started seeing more paper money than coins.27000:00:22,000 --> 00:00:27,300And the mayor ran away from the village, then there were no more coins, then the horses disappeared,27100:00:02,480 --> 00:00:05,440The sellers of Ernesto's Figs broke, Quique's peace dealers couldn't pay anyone27200:00:05,440 --> 00:00:08,880And they escaped at night, we're in ruins, Pepe.27300:00:08,880 --> 00:00:12,800And your side project asked Pepe, and Carmen's hair salon?27400:00:12,800 --> 00:00:15,160No, my thing was a failure, Horace said.27500:00:15,160 --> 00:00:18,600There are no horses to go to town to get some steering wheel and the ice melts27600:00:18,600 --> 00:00:22,080And Carmen doesn't have a client, you don't see that everyone's pulling their hair alone,27700:00:22,080 --> 00:00:23,880What do you want hairdressers for?27800:00:23,880 --> 00:00:28,480Pepe was silent, he couldn't believe what they were telling him.27900:00:04,240 --> 00:00:06,900Then Horace said, oh, for God's sake, I need something strong.28000:00:06,900 --> 00:00:11,220And Sabino asked, Pepe, you opened and you didn't open the bar you wanted to open.28100:00:11,220 --> 00:00:14,280And others came up to ask about the bar.28200:00:14,280 --> 00:00:17,540Pepe then discovered that without a horse,28300:00:17,540 --> 00:00:21,260No one would ever be able to go to his bar outside the town.28400:00:21,260 --> 00:00:26,280And he also realized that he could never return the 10,000 coins to anyone.28500:00:05,000 --> 00:00:05,880And then he saw Moncho in the middle of the square.28600:00:10,320 --> 00:00:14,360Moncho's two lean horses were the only animals left and they dragged three wagons with two wheels each in the shape of a train.28700:00:14,360 --> 00:00:17,480Many neighbors were riding on those cars.28800:00:17,480 --> 00:00:21,360And others were in a long line waiting to get up.28900:00:21,360 --> 00:00:24,760Moncho, Pepe asked, where are all these people going?29000:00:24,760 --> 00:00:27,000And Moncho said, where is he going?29100:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,400To the tub, to the moon.29200:00:03,440 --> 00:00:06,800Pepe saw a sign hanging on the broken source that said, "Moncho makes trips to the moon, exits, a coin,29300:00:06,800 --> 00:00:08,720I'll be back for free.29400:00:08,720 --> 00:00:12,040But Moncho asked, Pepe, did you know that everyone was going to stay29500:00:12,040 --> 00:00:13,320without a horse?29600:00:13,320 --> 00:00:14,440No, Moncho said.29700:00:14,440 --> 00:00:16,000I only did one thing.29800:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,200What I know is that people can go to a bar on horseback,29900:00:19,200 --> 00:00:22,160But no one can get drunk and ride a horse.30000:00:22,160 --> 00:00:25,240And since I don't take, I thought my business might be to take them30100:00:25,240 --> 00:00:27,000And bring them from the moon.30200:00:04,840 --> 00:00:04,880Then Pepe hugged Moncho, got in the first cart and yelled,30300:00:08,480 --> 00:00:08,520We're all going to the moon, free drinks the first night,30400:00:12,960 --> 00:00:13,000And the whole town went up and applauded even Nina,30500:00:15,720 --> 00:00:15,760She cheered for the end of the story.30600:00:19,320 --> 00:00:19,360And then I told my daughter to be careful,30700:00:22,840 --> 00:00:22,880Because in the real world, the Pepe stories,30800:00:26,360 --> 00:00:26,400Trying to open bars or monks stories30900:00:29,960 --> 00:00:00,000Who want to go to the moon and nobody understands them,31000:00:04,080 --> 00:00:06,640They're almost always projects that don't usually have happy endings like in children's stories,31100:00:06,640 --> 00:00:09,240Because in the middle there are quicks.31200:00:09,240 --> 00:00:13,200Mayors appear, hernexes appear and secretaries appear31300:00:13,200 --> 00:00:15,800And they always throw everything away.31400:00:15,800 --> 00:00:18,560But when any of these projects do work,31500:00:18,560 --> 00:00:20,800I told my daughter to finish,31600:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,520When these projects work,31700:00:22,520 --> 00:00:25,720When something magical happens and it works,31800:00:04,000 --> 00:00:00,000They're called dreams, and they're usually wonderful.